I Love Goshen Bicycle Criterium
description:
The I Heart Goshen Bicycle Criterium is an officially-sanctioned USA Cycling race held in evening the heart of downtown Goshen. Potential racers who are not currently licensed can log on to USA Cycling for license and participation criteria.

The 1-kilometer track features a fast, spectator-friendly race combining street racing and intense high-level competition in a spectacular urban environment. The I Heart Goshen Criterium has become one of Goshen\'s most popular monthly First Fridays events attracting hundreds of competitive cyclists and thousands of spectators.

Subaru Race the Bend Criterium Challenge Series
description: A 2 day criterium series Omnium in South Bend, IN.
course:
Saturday 16th: Howard Park, .6 mile loop on closed roads along St. joseph river with 3 corners and one sweeping turn.  One gradual climb and descent.
Sunday 17th: Downtown, .8 mile L-shaped counter clock-wise loop with 5 left and 1 right turn.  Mostly flat
notes:
1.) Organizer reserves the right to combine categories and cash awards based on participation
2.) Masters divisions run together but scored seperately 3.) 2nd race entry fee is $20
4.) $10 Late fee cahrged for day of event registration
5.) All USAC rules apply
6.) Standard USAC release along with license and ID required to race
7.) Registration will close 30 minutes prior to each event
8.) Wheel pit and free laps will be in effect
9.) Races will be held rain or shine

Indy Criterium Cycling Race & Festival
description:
The Indy Criterium, situated in the heart of Downtown Indianapolis, offers cyclists a unique opportunity to race the city streets that they would rarely have the chance to do otherwise.  Back by popular demand, racers can anticipate the same figure-8 course that made its debut in 2011.

 - Largest attended criterium race in Indiana in 2011
 - Opportunity to race multiple races
 - Podium ceremony for each category
 - Over $6,000 in cash and prizes
 - Food, Music, Expo
 - Beer Garden by Sun King Brewery
 - Community rides and family fun rides
 - Kids races
 - Juniors races
 - Tandem race
 - Bike messenger / courier relay race
 - Race kick off by Mayor Greg Ballard
 - Over 2,500 spectators!
course:
- 0.95 mile closed loop
 - Unique figure-8 course design
 - Smooth, wide course 
 - Course accommodates large, competitive fields
 - Race on the bricks of Monument Circle
notes:
- Call ups for first 20 registered in each category
 - Zipp 303 Wheel set ($2,700) raffle for pre-registered riders only (all categories!!)

Octoberfest CX Time Trial Series at IndyCycloplex
Bloomingcross
description: Scholars Inn Bakehouse cycling presents the OVCX BloomingCross!  Compete with the best that the Midwest has to offer on this challenging course in Bloomington, Indiana just a few minutes from Indiana University.   It\'s a technical but fun course with classic lines laid out on Karst Farm Park.  Several park restrooms are available.
course: New course layout at same venue as prior years!
registration: Pre-register at www.bikereg.com.  Pre-registration closes on Thursday, October 18 11:45 pm.  Race day registration begins at 9:00 am.  There is an additional $10 day of registration fee.  Registration is open until 30 minutes prior to the start of each event.  No additional fees for junior riders.
notes: Riders will be called up based on OVCX procedures.
directions: From SR 37 go West on SR 45/Bloomfield Road/2nd Street. Turn right on the stoplight on Airport Road then right again on Endwright Road.  The entrance to Karst Farm Park is on your left.  Ample parking is available.  More information here: http://www.karstfarmpark.com/info.php.
